</p></div>"}

Front wall with door. You will need to leave room in the frame for a door. The size of the door is dictated by what you are using the shed for, and what you need to move in and out. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/24/Build-a-Storage-Shed-Step-3Bullet3-Version-2.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Storage-Shed-Step-3Bullet3-Version-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/24/Build-a-Storage-Shed-Step-3Bullet3-Version-2.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Storage-Shed-Step-3Bullet3-Version-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
